text: Abadeh County () is a county in Fars Province in Iran. The capital of the county is Abadeh.Gitashenasi Province Atlas of Iran Atlas Gitashenasi Ostanhai Iran (طلس گیتاشناسی استان‌های ایران) At the 2016 census, the county's population was 100,831. and it is the most populous county in Northern Fars Province. The county has only one district: the Central District. The county has five cities: Abadeh, Soghad, Bahman, Izadkhvast, and Surmaq. == Administrative Subdivisions == == References == Category:Abadeh County
